# Keel Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vite + React 19 + TypeScript + TailwindCSS v4
- Backend: Express 5 + TypeScript (ESM)
- Database: PostgreSQL + Drizzle ORM
- Auth: BetterAuth

## Critical Rules
- ALL TypeScript imports MUST use .js extension (ESM): import { x } from "./foo.js"
- Shared types: import from "@keel/shared"
- Backend routes use requireAuth middleware for protected endpoints
- Frontend uses useAuth() hook for auth state
- TailwindCSS theme colors: keel-navy, keel-blue, keel-gray-{50,100,400,800,900}

## IMPORTANT: Use keel CLI for scaffolding
ALWAYS use these commands instead of manually creating files:
- npx @codaijs/keel generate route <name>  — creates route + auto-mounts in index.ts
- npx @codaijs/keel generate page <name>   — creates page + auto-adds to router.tsx
- npx @codaijs/keel generate email <name>  — creates template + auto-exports
- npx @codaijs/keel sail add <name>        — installs sail extension
- npm run check                   — verify all changes (typecheck + lint + test)

## Adding a Database Table
- Create schema in packages/backend/src/db/schema/<name>.ts, export from index.ts, run db:generate + db:migrate

## Verification
After any change, run: npm run check
